<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The call passes the address of the function parameter 'path' (a const char *). This permits lfs_dir_find to modify the pointer variable 'path' via the const char ** parameter (e.g. advance or reassign it), which would be modifying a function parameter and thus violates MISRA C 2023 Rule 17.8. To comply, make a local copy (e.g. const char *tmp = path;) and pass &tmp instead so the original parameter is not modified.
</scenario>

